<div class="body">
<h2>A Story Idea</h2>
 <p>While learning about databases, analogies are brought up which talk about gaurding the database with vigilance.</p>
 <p>These analogies include barriars which have doors. In order to open these doors, keys are required.</p>
 <p>Only authorized users have these keys. I thought, what would happen if a society turned another planet 
 <p>into a server and turned the home planet into its client, creating a <i>server-client</i> architecture.</p>
 <p>Eventually, the planet no longer needs the resources provided by the 'server' planet and the technology</p>
 <p>used to communicate between them becomes outdated. During this time, a cargo ship, while transporting</p>
 <p>goods to another system, is attacked by space pirates. They manage to escape but their communications port</p>
 <p>and consequently their navigation system are damaged, forcing them to land on an unknown but habitable</p>
 <p>planet glowing with computer activity. Except its a mega-super computer with a tight-nit security: THE server.</p>
 <p>There only hope is to communicate through the <i>server-software</i>, which can only reach the <i>client-planet</i>,</p>
 <p>for rescue. Will they be able to bypass <b>multiple levels of security barriers</b> to get help?</p><br>
 <p>Even if they could, would anyone hear them?</p><br>
</div>    
 <div style="background-color: grey">
   <img src="WorldClient.jpg" class="image pictureHandler" alt="Story client planet">
   <div id="picture1" class="caption">
     <h3>Literary device: Contrast</h3>
       <p>In a story, I like contrasts so I thought I'd throw some in my story.
       In the abandoned server-planet, the readers are exposed to a hard working group
       of adults researching to learn everything they can about the system
       in order to use the communication port. The structure that surrounds
       them is old, dark, cold, with clunky technology. And, its a survival
       situation. Take a look at the next image, 'The Mother Planet,' to see
       the strong contrast in the client-planet.</p>
    </div>
 </div>
<br>
<div class="body">
 <p>Unfortunately, the technology of the home planet has updated since the server-client project ended</p>
 <p> - making only one computer nerd with an interest in antiques, age 9 or 10, able to communicate with the</p>
 <p>survivors. When he finally receives a message from them, and understands it, will the grown-ups</p>
 <p>believe him?</p><br>
</div> 
 <div style="background-color:rgb(255,153,51)" padding="10px"> 
   <img src="StoryWorldMother.jpg" class="image pictureHandler" alt="Story mother planet"> 
   <div id="picture2" class="caption">
     <h3>The Mother Planet</h3>
     <p>In contrast, the home planet encompases a lazy group of adults. It is new, bright, warm, sunny,
     and has slick technology. The philosophy of the society is that no one needs to work
     because all of the work has already been done. They've strived to create paradise, a world where no one
     has to work again. There working class is entirely made of robots.</p>
   </div>
 </div>
<div class="body">  
 <br>
 <p>The boy genius will also need to go through security hoops in order to help his friends in distress</p>
 <p>such as an AI robot security set on stopping anyone from making exta-terrestrial communication.</p>
 <p>Below you have the option to make your own story by choosing the options below to get you started.</p>
 <p>Have fun with it!</p>
</div>
